<TEXT>
americans are becoming more tolerant of 
homosexuals and gay rights but that tolerance wanes the closer the 
issue gets to the home according to a national survey published 
monday 
the poll commissioned by the san francisco examiner showed 
that most heterosexuals 73 percent believe homosexuality should 
not be illegal but 57 percent disapprove of two people of the same 
sex living together as a married couple 
only 38 percent of the heterosexuals polled approved 5 percent 
said they didnt know 
and while only one in five americans knows someone with aids 
more than half of those polled said they are willing to pay 100 
more in taxes each year to find a cure for the deadly disease 
the examiner said the poll by teichner amp associates of fullerton 
is the most extensive us survey ever undertaken involving gay 
people and attitudes toward them 
the poll surveyed 3748 randomly selected people who said they 
are heterosexual and 400 who said they are homosexual or bisexual 
the margin of error ranged from plus or minus 17 percent for the 
heterosexual sample to 5 points either way for gay people polled 
the inescapable conclusion both nationally and in the bay 
area is that while people are fairly accepting of homosexual 
lifestyles in the theoretical sense they are less accepting the 
closer reality gets said pollster steve teichner 
for example one in three people polled said they would try to 
change a homosexual youths sexual orientation while only 15 
percent would try to do so with a gay friend 
other major conclusions of the poll were 
about two out of every three homosexual and heterosexual men 
and women believe discrimination of all kinds has dropped in the 
last decade 
women westerners liberals and jews tend to be more accepting 
of gays than others 
most of the respondents 81 percent said it would be 
discrimination to deny a person a job because of sexual orientation 
the south with two out of three straight people surveyed 
disapproving of samesex living arrangements is the least tolerent 
of homosexuality the west with almost half approving is the most 
tolerant the survey found 
</TEXT>
