<TEXT>
the smoot is no longer moot 
the smoot was invented in 1958 at the massachusetts institute of 
technology when freshman fraternity pledges were ordered to measure 
the length of harvard bridge using only chalk and the body of one 
oliver reed smoot jr the pranksters manhandled their fellow pledge 
endtoend like a ruler to measure the bridge 
the bridge markings maintained by lambda chi alpha pledges for 
30 years threatened to become extinct when the 1891 bridge 
recently was slated for a 165 million reconstruction 
however the metropolitan district commission and the department 
of public works decided the smoot should stay when the sidewalk was 
replaced 
as a result of the smoot withstanding the test of time it has 
become part of the folklore of the harvard bridge and as such is 
now under the protection of the mdc declared the agencys chief 
bridge engineer david lenhardt at a resmooting ceremony sunday 
on the night of the fraternity prank the bridge was found to be 
3644 smoots plus one ear 
out of the 14 pledges i had the distinction of being the 
shortest explained smoot who is 5 feet 7 inches 
and had the best name said peter s miller who was in 
charge of the chalk on that fateful night 
twice a year since freshman pledges have faithfully 
resmooted the bridge that links mit with boston marking each 
10smoot length with a gash of paint on the sidewalk 
the bridges new sidewalk is scored at 5foot 7inch intervals 
instead of the usual 6 feet which will make it easier for future 
pledges to repaint their smoot marks said charles madden senior 
vice president for martin continental construction co the 
contractor rebuilding the bridge 
smoot now an executive with a trade group in washington dc 
lay down to have miller chalk his measure on the new sidewalk 
although the original deed was done in the dark of night 
interrupted once by a patrolling police car that sent the pledges 
scurrying into the shrubs the resmooting was punctuated with 
flash bulbs and applause 
smoot and his son stephen mit class of 90 also posed in front 
of a bronze plaque that was donated by smoots class of 62 at 
their 25th class reunion 
it reads this plaque placed in honor of the smoot which 
joined the angstrom meter and light year as standards of length 
when in october 1958 the span of this bridge was measured using 
the body of oliver reed smoot mit 62 and found to be precisely 
3644 smoots and one ear 
reflecting back on the obscure act that has made him a local 
legend smoot concluded we did it under orders and we didnt 
enjoy it then but we sure as hell enjoy it now 
</TEXT>
