afford necessary nursing care lawyer virginia johnson said after 
lancaster county judge paul merritt issued the decree for the rev 
lincoln b justice and his wife rose marie 
this is not uncommon said johnson who represented mrs 
justice 56 
after mrs justice was paralyzed from the neck down in an 
automobile accident 10 years ago the couple had a specially 
designed wheelchairaccessible home built and coped using homemaker 
services 
but justice told merritt today that his wifes bout with 
pneumonia in january left her in need of 24hour care 
i cant work and provide that care justice said 
under a property settlement approved by the court mrs justice 
will remain in the lincoln home justice told reporters he expects 
to live in weeping water where he has been transferred and visit 
his exwife about once a week the town is about 35 miles away 
financial reasons were the main stress in this marriage 
johnson said rather than impoverish both husband and wife this 
will allow her to spend down her assets remain in her home and be 
