<TEXT>
the trespass trial of 155 antiabortion 
activists opened under the glare of floodlights monday with 
potential jurors and defendants sitting in a theater because no 
courtroom could hold all of them 
hillsborough county judge james d arnold consolidated the cases 
and rented the 300seat jaeb theater at the tampa performing arts 
complex for what is expected to be a weeklong trial 
arnold sat center stage at a makeshift judges bench while the 
95 prospective jurors occupied the first five rows the defendants 
took up the orchestra mezzanine and balcony seats of the theater 
designed as an intimate hall for nightclub acts and jazz ensembles 
prosecutors say the defendants broke the law april 15 when they 
tried to disrupt operations at the womens health center about 
1200 people organized by operation rescue an antiabortion group 
demonstrated at the clinic 
more than 180 were arrested and charged with trespass after 
warning a misdemeanor that carries a possibile maximum sentence of 
one year in prison and a 1000 fine some pleaded no contest in a 
deal with prosecutors and received six months probation the rest 
opted for trial 
jury candidates were bused to the arts complex attorneys 
expected to take all day to seat a sixmember jury 
outside four demonstrators representing both sides of the issue 
picketed peacefully 
the judge ruled earlier that the defendants wouldnt be allowed 
to argue that any trespass was justified and excusable because they 
were saving lives 
defense attorney gregory boyer had hoped to present what he said 
was evidence that many women arriving at the center on april 15 
were scheduled to have abortions and that most women deterred 
once are less likely to follow through with a second appointment 
he said the defense has been used in jury trials in similar cases 
elsewhere 
but arnold agreed with prosecutors that because abortion is 
legal in florida and a firsttrimester fetus is not considered a 
viable baby the defense is irrevelant and would become an 
emotional plea to jurors 
</TEXT>
