across the street from the white house on monday chanting singing 
and listening to speeches appealing for international help to 
stop the killing in beijing 
members of congress applauded president bushs decision to 
suspend military sales to china and to cut off contacts with 
chinese military leaders 
but a few said the united states should go further ending all 
us trade with china and stopping us investment in chinas 
economy 
