<DOCNO> AP890605-0175 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
publisher robert maxwell suspended publication 
of chinas official englishlanguage newspaper monday in europe 
saying he wouldnt honor the joint venture because of revulsion 
over the massacre in beijing 
chinas economic reforms have greatly improved the prospects 
of prosperity for its people the british newspaper magnate said 
in a statement released in new york but all that progress has 
been disfigured and nullified by the events of last weekend 
maxwell said it will be a standing disgrace to the name of 
china that the guns of the peoples army should have been turned so 
brutally upon the people themselves patience has always been one 
of the greatest chinese virtues patience was called for in 
beijing not bloody murder 
maxwell communication corp plc has been publishing and 
distributing the china daily in europe as part of an agreement with 
the chinese government which began the englishlanguage paper 
several years ago to broaden foreign awareness of the economic 
changes taking place in the country 
it is impossible for friends of china to say and do nothing in 
these circumstances maxwell said for my part i am suspending 
immediately the publication of china daily in europe i hope it 
will not be long before i can resume but that depends on a drastic 
reversal of the course upon which the chinese leadership has 
embarked 
</TEXT>
