<TEXT>
economists said major banks reduction of their 
prime interest rates by a halfpoint to 11 percent did not 
necessarily signal a fullscale plunge in interest rates for the 
near future 
experts said mondays cut in the prime was more an attempt by 
the banks to attract business than an indication they expect the 
federal reserve to push market rates sharply lower to forestall an 
economic recession 
the prime is a benchmark used to set interest rates on a variety 
of bank credit ranging from corporate loans to adjustable home 
mortgages 
</TEXT>
